# Testing Rules (generic)

Repo-specific launchers, Blender bindings, and pytest markers live in project `testing.instructions.md`.

## Test code placement (mandatory)

All testing-related code lives under the module's **`test/`** subdirectory — aggregators, discovery, parity scaffolding, path helpers, output logging, fixtures, runners.

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| **MUST** | Place new test helpers in `<module>/test/` (sister scripts, `aggregator.py`, `parity.py`, `paths.py`, …) |
| **NEVER** | Create new `test_support/` folders |
| **Migrate** | When touching legacy `test_support/` code, move it into the owning module's `test/` |
| **Exception** | Repo-root `tests/` — integration launchers only (`blender_headless.py`, `run_tests.py`, `lks_test_launcher.py`) |

```
✅ operators/bake_ops/engine/test/aggregator.py       # shared bake-engine test helpers
✅ operators/bake_ops/engine/map_types/curvature/test/curvature_runner.py  # type-local
❌ operators/bake_ops/engine/map_types/test_support/aggregator.py
```

## Sister tests

Every Python module script gets a **sister test script** in a sibling `test/` folder at the same module/submodule level:

```
<module>/
├── my_script.py
└── test/
    └── my_script_test.py
```

| Type | Pattern |
|------|---------|
| Module / helper | `<source_stem>_test.py` |
| Operator class | `<OperatorClass>_test.py` |

## Aggregator pyramid (`test_all.py`)

Every `test/` folder exposes **`test_all.py`** — the single runnable entry for that level.

| Level | `test_all.py` runs |
|-------|---------------------|
| **Leaf** | Sibling `*_test.py` scripts in this folder |
| **Stem** | Local tests **and** each child submodule's `test/test_all.py` |
| **Root** | `<workspace>/test/test_all.py` — all top-level module aggregators |

**Leaf → stem:** parent invokes child aggregators; do not maintain duplicate test lists at every level.

## Test data (per test folder)

```
test/
├── data/
│   ├── in/     # inputs for this folder
│   └── out/    # outputs for this folder only
```

| Kind | Path | Notes |
|------|------|-------|
| **Inputs** | `test/data/in/` | May also read shared workspace assets when multiple tests need them |
| **Outputs** | `test/data/out/` | **Local only** — each `*_test.py` and local `test_all.py` writes here |
| **Parent composites** | parent `test/data/out/` | Parent `test_all.py` assembling grids/composites reads child `test/data/out/`, writes aggregates to **parent** `test/data/out/` — never into child outs |

Small inline fixtures stay in the test file. Large/binary inputs belong under `test/data/in/`.

## Hygiene (clear before run)

- Each `*_test.py` clears **its own** artifacts in local `test/data/out/` before generation.
- Each `test_all.py` clears **only its own** local `test/data/out/` at batch begin (child aggregators skip when `LKS_TEST_AGGREGATOR_CHILD=1`).
- Parent `test_all.py` compositing reads child `test/data/out/` but does **not** wipe child outs between subprocesses.

## Permissions

- Tests **may hardcode** paths to workspace resources/assets.
- Tests **may generate or use** data at runtime.

## Coverage & failure mode

Per public function: happy path, edge case, error case where applicable. Complex functions: parametrized boundaries.

Tests MUST NOT stop on first failure — accumulate failures, report at end, single non-zero exit.

## Pragmatic exemptions

No sister test for files containing ONLY: enums, dataclasses (no logic), constants, re-exports.

## Qt / pytest overlay (when applicable)

| Type | Pattern |
|------|---------|
| Qt GUI test | `@pytest.mark.gui` on `*_test.py` |
| Visual QA demo | `demo_<component>_ui_gui.py` (not pytest) |
| Primary run | `pytest -m gui -v`; headless CI: `QT_QPA_PLATFORM=offscreen` |
